text: Michael D. Dubke (born April 18, 1970) is an American entrepreneur and political aide. He was the White House Communications Director for U.S. President Donald Trump until his resignation on June 2, 2017. ==References== Category:1970 births Category:Living people Category:Politicians from New York (state) Category:Businesspeople from New York (state) Category:White House Communications Directors Category:Republican Party (United States) politicians
